    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-06-22T11:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-06-22T11:00:00-05:00" n="339"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d339">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 European War 1939/4094: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Egypt</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Hare</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Cairo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-06-22T18:00:00+02:00"
                            >June 22, 1940—6 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received June 23—5:58 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>117. My telegram No. 115, June 22, 8 a.m.<note n="8" xml:id="d339fn8">Not
                        printed.</note> An official communiqué issued this afternoon states this
                    morning’s air raid warning in Cairo was a false alarm and that the planes fired
                    upon were Royal Air Force units. Several civilian casualties from anti-aircraft
                    fire reported.</p>
                <pb facs="0483" n="471" xml:id="pg_471"/>
                <p>Another communiqué states that 2 persons were killed and 23 wounded during last
                    night’s bombing in Alexandria. Consul there reports no American casualties.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hare</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
